# CSS Setup and Structure

This rule describes **how global styling is set up**, how **fonts** connect to Tailwind, and how **components** should use Tailwind vs shared CSS. Step-by-step token and font changes: `.cursor/skills/extend-design-tokens/SKILL.md`. References include `src/app/globals.css`, `@/app/lib/fonts.ts`, `@/app/layout.tsx`, and `@/app/(classes)/_components/Course/**`.

## 1) Global setup (`src/app/globals.css`)

**Single entry:** Tailwind v4 is activated with `@import "tailwindcss"` at the top.

**Preserve this top-to-bottom structure:**

1. **`@import "tailwindcss"`** — required first line.
2. **`@theme`** — custom breakpoints (`--breakpoint-*` reset, then `3xs` … `2xl`). Use these names in responsive utilities (`max-md:`, `md:`, `lg:`, etc.).
- Use template:
```css
@theme {
  --breakpoint-*: initial;
  --breakpoint-3xs: 20rem; /* (320px) Extra small phones  */
  --breakpoint-2xs: 30rem; /* (480px) Extra small phones */
  --breakpoint-xs: 35rem; /* (560px) Small phones */
  --breakpoint-sm: 40rem; /* (640px) Small phones */
  --breakpoint-md: 48rem; /* (768px) Tablets */
  --breakpoint-lg: 55rem; /* (880px) Small laptops */
  --breakpoint-xl: 60rem; /* (960px) Small laptops */
  --breakpoint-2xl: 75rem; /* (1200px) Desktop */
}
```
3. **`:root`** — raw semantic palette (`--primary`, `--screenWhite`, `--error`, …). Add new brand colors here first.
Use template:
```css 
:root {
  --primary: /*primary color*/;
  --secondary: /*secondary color*/;
  --screenBlack: #0d0d0d;
  --screenWhite: #fdfdfd;
  --screenGrey: #141414;
  --error: #ff1744;
}
```
4. **`@theme inline`** — bridge to Tailwind: `--color-*` from `:root` vars, `--font-title|subtitle|body|button|input|error` pointing at `--font-*` variables produced by `next/font` on `<body>`.
5. **`@layer base`** — optional global element rules; keep minimal.
6. **`@layer components`** — reusable patterns used across routes (`.conBox`, `.btn`, `.formInput`, `.loadingSpinner`, `.navLink`, form layout helpers). Put here when **two or more** features need the same class.
7. **`@layer utilities`** — small domain-driven utility classes (letter grades, assignment type tints, behavior bands). Reference them from JSX with plain class names (e.g. `finalLetterGrade`, `assignment.type`, `noGrade`).
8. **`body`** — page background and text color from CSS variables; keep aligned with app shell.

**Do not** import `globals.css` from any file other than root `src/app/layout.tsx`. Do not duplicate token definitions in random CSS files—extend `:root` / `@theme inline` or use Tailwind utilities.

## 2) Fonts (`@/app/lib/fonts.ts`)

- Register each face with `next/font/google` and **`variable: "--font-<kebab-name>"`** so it matches `--font-*` references in `@theme inline` (e.g. `--font-sour-gummy`, `--font-balsamiq-sans`, `--font-roboto-flex`, `--font-delius`, `--font-geist-sans`, `--font-geist-mono`).
- Export one **camelCase** constant per font (`sourGummy`, `balsamiqSans`, …).

When adding a new font:

1. Add the `next/font` export with a new `--font-*` variable name.
2. Map it in `globals.css` `@theme inline` (e.g. a new `--font-…` role if needed).
3. Wire the `.variable` class on `<body>` in `layout.tsx` (see below).

## 3) Root layout wiring (`@/app/layout.tsx`)

- Import `./globals.css` once.
- Import all font exports from `@/app/lib/fonts`.
- On `<html>`, keep `lang` appropriate for the app.
- On `<body>`, concatenate **every** font’s `.variable` class with global utilities, matching the project pattern:

  - `antialiased`, `min-h-screen`, `bg-screenWhite`, `font-body` (maps theme body font).

This makes `--font-*` available everywhere so `font-title`, `font-subtitle`, `font-body`, etc. resolve in Tailwind classes.

## 4) Tailwind usage in components (Course reference)

<!-- `@/app/(classes)/_components/Course/**` is the reference for mixing **layout utilities**, **theme tokens**, **component-layer classes**, and **utility-layer domain classes**. -->

**Layout and spacing:** Prefer Tailwind for flex/grid, gaps, widths, padding, and responsive breakpoints (`flex`, `max-md:flex-col`, `w-[95%]`, `md:w-[40%]`, `gap-2`, …).

**Semantic colors and typography from theme:** Use token-backed utilities such as `bg-screenWhite`, `text-zinc-500`, `font-title`, `font-subtitle`, `font-body` instead of hard-coding hex colors for brand roles.

**Shared component classes from `globals.css`:** Use `@layer components` classes where they already exist—for example `.whiteBox` for bordered cards, `.btn` / `.quarterSelect` / `.quarterSelectLabel` in `Options.tsx`, form patterns in modals elsewhere.

**Domain utilities from `globals.css`:** As an example, in `Grades.tsx` / `Assignments.tsx` / `Behaviors.tsx`, dynamic classes like letter grades (`A`, `B`, …), `noGrade`, or assignment type keys (`HW`, `CW`, `Q`, …) are applied as **string templates** when they map to `@layer utilities` definitions. Keep those class names in sync with `globals.css` only—do not redefine the same tints in feature CSS.

**Stable hooks for structure/testing:** As an example, Course tree uses consistent `id` / class prefixes (`titleConC`, `classConC`, …). Prefer Tailwind for visual layout; use `id` sparingly for meaningful regions when useful.

## 5) Feature-level CSS files (optional)

- Prefer **Tailwind + globals layers** first.
- If a feature needs scoped rules not worth globalizing, add a colocated file such as `Course/Course.css` and import it only from components that need it (e.g. `Announcements.tsx` importing `./Course.css`).
- Feature CSS must **not** redefine theme tokens; use `var(--primary)` / theme colors if you need raw CSS, or rely on existing CSS variables from `:root`.

## 6) Decision checklist

| Need | Where it goes |
|------|----------------|
| New brand color / font role for whole app | `:root` + `@theme inline` + `fonts.ts` + `layout.tsx` body classes |
| Reused button/card/form row | `@layer components` in `globals.css` |
| Grade/type/behavior tint class | `@layer utilities` in `globals.css` |
| One-off layout in a screen | Tailwind `className` on that component |
| Rules used only inside one feature folder | Optional `Feature.css` next to the feature, imported locally |

## 7) Anti-patterns

- Importing `globals.css` outside `src/app/layout.tsx`.
- New `--color-*` usage in JSX without adding the token to `:root` / `@theme inline`.
- New font in `fonts.ts` without `.variable` on `<body>` and without `@theme inline` mapping.
- Large bespoke `.css` files that duplicate what Tailwind + `globals.css` layers already provide.
